<HEAD>Eight Killed in Plane Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All eight people aboard were killed when a small
plane crashed in southern China's Hunan province after spraying
pesticides, the official Xinhua News Agency said today.
   The report said the Yun-5 utility biplane crashed Monday in a
mountainous area of Wangcheng county during a return flight to the
provincial capital of Changsha. The four crew members and four
workers aboard were reported killed.
