<DATELINE>HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A billboard advertising company says it
will mark the 20th anniversary of Robert F. Kennedy's assassination
with 38 billboards around the country recalling his life.
   The memorials are to be unveiled Wednesday at sites including
one near the Los Angeles hotel where Kennedy was shot June 5, 1968,
after winning the California Democratic presidential primary.
   Patrick Media Group said in a release from its Hartford office
that branch offices are responsible for creating the displays in
their respective regions. But each billboard will carry a black
