<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Kenya-AxKillings     05-31 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Kenya-Ax Killings,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kenyan Teen Hacks Six People To Death With Ax</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-ager killed six people with an ax,
including four of his relatives, before he fell to his death into a
ditch while fleeing a village mob, newspapers reported Tuesday.
   The killings occurred May 26 in the remote village of Linjoka in
northern Kenya, but the incident was not reported until Tuesday.
Linjoka is 135 miles north of Nairobi, Kenya's capital.
   Witnesses said 17-year-old William M'Maroo's victims included
his stepmother, his 4-year-old stepsister, his stepmother's uncle,
her cousin, a neighbor, and another man.
   Newspapers said M'Maroo fled when 600 villagers gathered at the
scene and gave chase. M'Maroo reportedly fell into a 40-foot deep
gully while running away and was fatally injured.
   There was no motive for the attacks.
   One witness said M'Maroo had arrived home Wednesday night from
Mombasa, Kenya's second largest town. He said the youth had gone to
the Indian Ocean port town to sell miraa, a popular leaf chewed for
its narcotic effect.
</TEXT>
