<1ST_LINE>r a AM-StateSymbols-Glance 1stLd-Writethru a0683 05-31 0476</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-State Symbols-Glance, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0683,0487</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Some Symbols Debated in Recent Legislative Sessions</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS anthropodic to arthropodic in Maryland item on
Baltimore checkerspot butterfly.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some of the measures that have come before state
legislatures this session:
   CALIFORNIA _ Senate passed and Assembly is considering bill to
make the West Coast Swing the official state dance of California;
Assembly passed but Senate put off a bill to make banana slug the
official state mollusk.
   FLORIDA _ House voted to make key lime pie the official state
pie, but Senate Rules Chairman Dempsey Barron favors sweet potato
pie; House also named Mayakka Fine Sand as the Official State Soil,
but measure faces uncertain future in the Senate.
   GEORGIA _ Tiger swallowtail named official state butterfly.
   HAWAII _ Legislature approved bills making the nene, a native
goose, the state bird, and the Hibiscus the state flower; bills are
before Gov. John Waihee for approval.
   IDAHO _ Hagerman Horse Fossil was named the state fossil; Senate
rejected moves to name The Silver Tipped Sagebrush the state bush
and the white sturgeon the state fish.
   KENTUCKY _ Bill Monroe's ``Blue Moon of Kentucky'' was named the
official bluegrass song. ``My Old Kentucky Home'' remains THE state
song.
   LOUISIANA _ Legislature considering a resolution naming a
poster, called ``Louisiana, the Spice of Life'' and designed by a
woman in Rapides Parish, the official state poster.
   MARYLAND _ Legislature refused to change the official state
sport from jousting to lacrosse; also rejected a bill to make the
blue crab the state crustacean and to reclassify the Baltimore
checkerspot butterfly from the state arthropodic emblem to the
state insect.
   MASSACHUSETTS _ House considering bill to name corn the official
state vegetable; House has passed and sent to Senate measure naming
the tabby cat the official cat of the commonwealth.
   NEW YORK _ Legislature passed bill earlier this month that would
make the sea scallop the state seashell.
   OKLAHOMA _ ``Faded Rose,'' by the late Tulsa resident Bob Wills,
was named the official country and western song.
   PENNSYLVANIA _ House committee approved legislation that would
name phacops rana, a long-extinct small water animal, the state
fossil; House passed but Senate has not acted on bill naming
Photuris pensylvanica the state firefly.
   SOUTH CAROLINA _ Bill making praying mantis the state insect
awaiting governor's signature; joint conference committee
considering bill to make the the loggerhead sea turtle the state
reptile.
   SOUTH DAKOTA _ The triceratops, a plant-eating dinosaur, was
named the official fossil and Black Hills gold was named the
official jewelry.
   TENNESSEE _ Legislature named the catfish the official
commercial fish and the largemouth bass the official game fish.
   UTAH _ Legislature designated the allosaurus the state fossil.
   WEST VIRGINIA _ Senate passed but House did not consider naming
the monarch butterfly the state insect.
</TEXT>
