<HEAD>Reagans, Gorbachevs Exchange Gifts</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SUSANNE M. SCHAFER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the list of the gifts exchanged at the
U.S.-Soviet summit, as provided by the White House:
   For General Secretary Mikhail Gorbachev from President Reagan:
   _``The Rattlesnake'' by Christine Roussel, a bronze statue, line
for line after the cast of Frederick Remington's ``The
Rattlesnake,'' Reagan's favorite. The sculpture is 23{ inches high
and is presented on a wooden base with the following inscription:
   ``To his Excellency Mikhail Sergeyvich Gorbachev, General
Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of the
Soviet Union, From Ronald Reagan, President of the United States of
America, May 1988.''
   For Raisa Gorbachev from Nancy Reagan:
   _A cotton quilt made by Julia Spidell of Sparta, N.C. The quilt
has a white background with four rows of geometric-shaped baskets
filled with red flowers. It has a floral-patterned border.
