   _An exact replica of the Kremlin, on a scale of 1:1000, with all
its historical sights and with the adjoining Red Square and St.
Basil's Cathedral. It was made with the aid of a of bronze casting
technique by A.N. Lysenkov, the chief artist of the Balashova
Experimental Plant of Decorative Casting in Mytishchi (Moscow
Region). Lysenkov is a well-known master of bronze miniature models.
   For Nancy Reagan from Raisa Gorbachev:
   _The ``Ballet'' coffee set, with service for six. It was made at
the Lomonosov Ceramic Works in Leningrad from bone porcelain in one
copy. The artists are A. Leporskaya, a merited artist of the
Russian Federation, and Y. Zhgirov.
