<HEAD>Australian Jazz Singer Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ricky May, a leading Australian jazz
singer, collapsed and died early Wednesday minutes after being
given a standing ovation at the opening night of his new show at
the Regent Hotel in Sydney.
   The New Zealand-born May, 44, walked off stage and was heading
to his room to change when he was stricken with what appeared to be
a heart attack outside the elevator, a hotel spokesman said.
