<HEAD>London Shares Down 4.1 Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks fell by midday today, reflecting what
brokers called a lack of enthusiasm after a long weekend.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was down 4.1
points, or 0.2 percent, at 1,779.6, by early afternoon London time.
Monday was a bank holiday in Britain.
   Volume was light at 224.3 million shares compared with 197.5
million shares at the same time Friday.
   Dealers said the greatest activity was in shares of Cadbury
Schweppes PLC, which jumped the equivalent of 24 cents $7.73. There
was market speculation the company could follow Rowntree PLC,
another confectionery maker, as a takeover target.
   General Cinema Corp. of the United States has amassed an 18.4
percent stake in Cadbury.
