<HEAD>Stop & Shop Seeks To Sell Regional Bradlees Stores</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Stop & Shop Cos. said Tuesday it plans to sell
the southern division of its Bradlees department stores, which
operates 58 stores in Pennsylvania, Maryland, Washington, Virginia
and North Carolina.
   Stop & Shop said the stores were strong performers but that the
company, the target of a recent takeover attempt, wanted to
concentrate both its supermarket and department store operations in
the Northeast.
