sale, Stop & Shop said in a statement. The 58 stores for sale
generated revenues of $635 million in the last fiscal year, the
company said.
   Stop & Shop has 133 supermarkets in Connecticut, Massachusetts,
Rhode Island and New York. If the 58 Bradlees stores are sold, the
company still would own 110 Bradlees in Connecticut, Maine,
Massachusetts, New Hampshire, Mew Jersey and New York.
