   The stock market surged today as trading resumed
after the three-day Memorial holiday weekend.
   Volume was fairly strong, but more than half of the shares
traded on the New York Stock Exchange involved the stocks of two
utility companies whose dividend eligibility dates are approaching.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks, which fell 10.31
